Privacy Policy

Your privacy is very important to CattleFax. The personal and business information you provide is only for our internal use.

As you browse www.CattleFax.com, tracking cookies may be placed on your computer so that we can understand what you are interested in and your on-site traffic consumption patterns. We may collect information including IP address, internet service provider, businesses associated with the ISP, amount of time spent on site and pages visited.

If you have provided contact information via a web form, you authorize us to associate your voluntarily-provided contact information with your on-site usage patterns. Your information will not be shared, rented or sold to third-parties for use outside of CattleFax (its employees, consultants and agents) unless so ordered by a court of law.

Please Contact Us if you have further questions about how CattleFax will use this information.
